    "body": "Currently, builds of libevent in depends, using CMake, fail on some systems, like Alpine, with the following:\r\n```bash\r\n/bitcoin/depends/work/build/aarch64-unknown-linux-musl/libevent/2.1.12-stable-1516ed47ea8/evmap.c: In function 'evmap_signal_add_':\r\n/bitcoin/depends/work/build/aarch64-unknown-linux-musl/libevent/2.1.12-stable-1516ed47ea8/evmap.c:456:31: error: 'NSIG' undeclared (first use in this function)\r\n  456 |         if (sig < 0 || sig >= NSIG)\r\n```\r\n\r\nFrom what I can tell the `GNU_SOURCE` \"detection\" in libevents CMake build system, never? really worked, primarily relies on looking for a deprecated define, and it's not clear what a nice fix is. So, opening this as a Draft, while looking at fixing this upstream. In any case, we'll need to do something for the `28.x` branch.",
